13
00:01:21,604 --> 00:01:22,891
Here we go.

14
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:51,672
Hey!

15
00:01:52,138 --> 00:01:54,157
I heard what you said on the time capsule.

16
00:01:54,158 --> 00:01:55,226
Look, Russ...

17
00:02:00,481 --> 00:02:02,068
Nice locker, boozer.

18
00:02:40,186 --> 00:02:41,592
Call 911.

19
00:02:43,160 --> 00:02:46,614
Code red, code red. This is not a drill.

20
00:02:46,615 --> 00:02:50,916
All students to a designated lockdown area. This is a code red.

21
00:02:50,917 --> 00:02:54,263
He puts a shot up and scores! The Ravens are down by one.

22
00:02:54,264 --> 00:02:58,366
Okay, this is a code red. Please, go to a designated lockdown area

23
00:02:58,367 --> 00:03:01,115
or exit the school immediately.

24
00:03:07,784 --> 00:03:08,864
Peyton?

25
00:03:09,293 --> 00:03:10,310
Peyton!

26
00:03:11,444 --> 00:03:12,502
Peyton!

27
00:03:16,907 --> 00:03:18,197
What the hell?

28
00:03:20,216 --> 00:03:21,059
Hey.

29
00:03:21,060 --> 00:03:22,990
Somebody has a gun inside, and they're shooting.

30
00:03:22,991 --> 00:03:23,909
Haley!

31
00:03:23,910 --> 00:03:26,180
Oh, my god. Everybody back on the bus!

32
00:03:26,181 --> 00:03:27,446
I lost Peyton. I don't know where she is.

33
00:03:27,447 --> 00:03:29,655
She was right there, and a shot went off, and now she's gone.

34
00:03:29,656 --> 00:03:31,256
W-w-wait. Peyton was shot?

35
00:03:31,257 --> 00:03:34,137
No, I don't know. She was right behind me. We were by the library.

36
00:03:34,138 --> 00:03:35,431
Haley's in the tutor center.

37
00:03:35,432 --> 00:03:39,839
All students, on the bus! Code red! Now! Let's move! Come on!

38
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:42,980
Nathan, get your ass on that bus.

39
00:03:44,218 --> 00:03:45,535
- I'll get him, coach.
- Luke!

40
00:03:45,536 --> 00:03:47,170
Brooke, I'll be right back.

41
00:03:47,351 --> 00:03:48,541
Nathan!

42
00:03:48,811 --> 00:03:49,962
Boys!

43
00:03:50,279 --> 00:03:51,459
Boys!

44
00:03:52,923 --> 00:03:54,362
Get off me, man.

45
00:03:55,258 --> 00:03:56,667
Haley's inside.

46
00:03:58,426 --> 00:03:59,796
Nathan!

47
00:04:01,635 --> 00:04:02,887
Lucas!

48
00:04:03,166 --> 00:04:04,281
Lucas!

49
00:04:04,834 --> 00:04:06,058
Get on the bus.

50
00:04:06,146 --> 00:04:08,307
Drive, drive! Go, go!

51
00:04:23,667 --> 00:04:26,464
Okay, everybody just stay down and stay calm.

52
00:04:26,465 --> 00:04:27,775
We're safe here.

53
00:04:50,370 --> 00:04:51,578
Got a plan?

54
00:04:51,579 --> 00:04:54,899
Yeah. I'm going to the tutor center, and I'm gonna get Haley.

55
00:04:57,843 --> 00:04:58,869
What are you doing?

56
00:04:58,870 --> 00:04:59,835
The plan sucks.

57
00:04:59,836 --> 00:05:00,729
You got a better one?

58
00:05:00,730 --> 00:05:02,730
Yeah, we turn around and let the police handle this.

59
00:05:02,731 --> 00:05:05,484
Police are gonna wait and game plan. They always do that.

60
00:05:05,485 --> 00:05:06,774
And what?

61
00:05:06,785 --> 00:05:09,641
You're gonna stop a bullet with a baseball bat?

62
00:05:09,642 --> 00:05:13,092
Nathan -- Nathan, someone has a gun in here.

63
00:05:13,093 --> 00:05:15,983
Lucas, I know that, okay? I know this is stupid.

64
00:05:15,984 --> 00:05:17,743
But what if something happens to Haley, huh?

65
00:05:17,744 --> 00:05:19,874
What if we walk away and something happens to Haley?

66
00:05:19,875 --> 00:05:21,554
Are you gonna live with that?

67
00:05:21,775 --> 00:05:24,461
Most heroes are dead, Nate.

68
00:05:26,047 --> 00:05:28,403
It's Haley, Lucas.

69
00:05:30,717 --> 00:05:32,299
We need to get out of here.

70
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:35,939
No, we need to stay put. It's procedure -- lockdown.

71
00:05:35,940 --> 00:05:37,403
We have to wait until it's safe.

72
00:05:37,404 --> 00:05:39,260
And I'm saying lockdown is crap.

73
00:05:39,261 --> 00:05:41,855
If whoever's out there's a student, they know where we're at.

74
00:05:41,856 --> 00:05:43,386
What about the windows?

75
00:05:43,387 --> 00:05:45,433
We could break the windows and get out.

76
00:05:45,434 --> 00:05:48,977
No, it just goes to a courtyard. It's enclosed. It's just for light.

77
00:05:48,978 --> 00:05:51,249
Yeah, besides, we get to breaking all the windows,

78
00:05:51,250 --> 00:05:53,200
all we do is draw attention to ourselves.

79
00:05:53,201 --> 00:05:54,752
You don't think a locked door is gonna tell

80
00:05:54,753 --> 00:05:56,911
whatever psycho is out there that we're in here?

81
00:05:56,912 --> 00:05:59,241
Why would you call him psycho?

82
00:06:02,550 --> 00:06:05,911
Something to do with them trying to kill us all, fat ass.

83
00:06:09,736 --> 00:06:11,278
Look, there's blood.

84
00:06:15,038 --> 00:06:16,646
Nate, it could be Peyton.

85
00:06:16,755 --> 00:06:18,260
You don't know that.

86
00:06:18,261 --> 00:06:19,822
Well, it's someone.

87
00:06:19,823 --> 00:06:22,117
The  library doors don't lock. It's not safe.

88
00:06:22,118 --> 00:06:25,022
Lucas, I have to find Haley.

89
00:06:25,254 --> 00:06:26,359
I know.

90
00:06:27,697 --> 00:06:28,841
Okay.

91
00:06:31,202 --> 00:06:32,284
Nathan...

92
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:36,523
Yeah.

93
00:06:37,131 --> 00:06:38,417
You too, man.

94
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:44,908
Peyton. Hey, it's okay.

95
00:07:44,909 --> 00:07:46,170
Ow, my leg!

96
00:07:46,234 --> 00:07:48,583
I got cut by some glass.

97
00:07:48,881 --> 00:07:51,534
Lucas, I lost Brooke. I'm sorry.

98
00:07:51,535 --> 00:07:54,469
She's fine. She's fine. But, okay, you're not.

99
00:07:54,470 --> 00:07:56,700
Um, we got to get you somewhere safe. Come on.

100
00:07:56,701 --> 00:07:59,987
No, I can't. I can't walk. I tried.

101
00:08:00,471 --> 00:08:01,697
Okay.

102
00:08:03,939 --> 00:08:04,829
Okay.

103
00:08:04,830 --> 00:08:06,877
No, don't leave me, please.

104
00:08:06,878 --> 00:08:09,418
No, look, hey, I'm gonna go block the entrance, all right?

105
00:08:09,419 --> 00:08:14,828
We'll -- we'll just hide, all right, wait this out, okay?

106
00:08:15,063 --> 00:08:17,068
Listen to me, okay?

107
00:08:17,817 --> 00:08:19,803
I'm not leaving you, Peyton.

108
00:08:21,703 --> 00:08:22,848
I won't.

109
00:08:23,412 --> 00:08:25,286
I won't, okay?

110
00:08:39,365 --> 00:08:40,836
Dude, what's happening?

111
00:08:40,837 --> 00:08:43,103
Mouth, what are you doing here?

112
00:08:43,104 --> 00:08:45,284
- I was in the --
- Shh!

113
00:08:46,842 --> 00:08:50,161
I was in the A/V room, and I come out, and it's like "dawn of the dead."

114
00:08:50,162 --> 00:08:51,658
Mouth, don't say  "dead."

115
00:08:51,934 --> 00:08:53,432
Someone's got a gun in the school.

116
00:08:53,433 --> 00:08:54,470
What?

117
00:08:55,241 --> 00:08:56,334
We got to get out of here.

118
00:08:56,335 --> 00:08:58,058
Yeah, you got to get out of here.

119
00:08:58,059 --> 00:08:59,907
I got to go get Haley.

120
00:09:03,843 --> 00:09:05,393
I'll stay with you.

121
00:09:06,268 --> 00:09:07,426
Let's go.

122
00:09:12,696 --> 00:09:14,192
No signal.

123
00:09:14,197 --> 00:09:16,002
All  circuits busy.

124
00:09:26,552 --> 00:09:27,705
It's Nathan.

125
00:09:27,706 --> 00:09:29,516
No way. We don't know it's him.

126
00:09:29,517 --> 00:09:30,766
No, it's his driver's license.

127
00:09:30,767 --> 00:09:33,614
How do you know somebody didn't kill him and take his I.D.?

128
00:09:33,630 --> 00:09:36,454
Okay, you're the one that said this is a lockdown, every man for himself.

129
00:09:36,465 --> 00:09:37,863
She can't leave him out there.

130
00:09:37,864 --> 00:09:39,427
Don't open it.

131
00:09:40,470 --> 00:09:42,498
- Do not open that door.
- Shut up! Shut up!

132
00:09:46,301 --> 00:09:47,682
Always...

133
00:09:47,683 --> 00:09:48,882
And forever.

134
00:09:50,243 --> 00:09:51,082
It's him.

135
00:09:51,083 --> 00:09:52,683
No way. Get away from the door.

136
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:56,881
Look, if she say it's him, it's him. Open the door.

137
00:09:59,380 --> 00:10:01,118
God, come here. Are you okay?

138
00:10:01,119 --> 00:10:02,624
Yeah. What's going on out there?

139
00:10:02,625 --> 00:10:05,446
I don't know, but we're getting out of here, okay? All of us. Let's go.

140
00:10:05,447 --> 00:10:06,758
Don't.

141
00:10:11,118 --> 00:10:13,048
Nobody's going anywhere.

142
00:10:22,067 --> 00:10:23,765
Get away from the door.

143
00:10:24,060 --> 00:10:24,902
Jimmy?

144
00:10:24,902 --> 00:10:25,843
Do it, Mouth!

145
00:10:25,852 --> 00:10:27,138
All right, all right. Just chill out.

146
00:10:27,134 --> 00:10:28,911
Everyone, get away from the door.

147
00:10:29,171 --> 00:10:30,638
Oh, Jimmy, what'd you do?

148
00:10:30,639 --> 00:10:31,840
Move back, Skills.

149
00:10:31,841 --> 00:10:33,388
Or what, you gonna shoot me?

150
00:10:33,389 --> 00:10:34,747
We used to be friends, dog.

151
00:10:34,748 --> 00:10:36,108
Yeah, used to be.

152
00:10:36,109 --> 00:10:38,230
So it's like that? All right.

153
00:10:38,231 --> 00:10:39,838
Jim, you can't do this.

154
00:10:39,839 --> 00:10:41,076
It's a little late for that, Mouth.

155
00:10:41,077 --> 00:10:42,267
I can't be here.

156
00:10:42,268 --> 00:10:44,554
Look, man, just let us go. I'm sorry I called you "fat ass."

157
00:10:44,555 --> 00:10:46,456
It's a little late for that, too.

158
00:10:47,922 --> 00:10:49,604
How about you, hero?

159
00:10:50,256 --> 00:10:51,815
Are you scared?

160
00:10:52,574 --> 00:10:54,899
Yeah, I'm scared.

161
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:57,758
Good. Welcome to my world.

162
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:00,444
All right.

163
00:11:04,713 --> 00:11:06,383
All right, this is what we're gonna do.

164
00:11:06,384 --> 00:11:08,836
You're gonna tape a line down the center of the room.

165
00:11:09,978 --> 00:11:11,343
Go on!

166
00:11:11,645 --> 00:11:13,378
Why are you doing this?

167
00:11:13,651 --> 00:11:15,524
You're Abby Brown, right?

168
00:11:15,875 --> 00:11:17,551
What's my name?

169
00:11:18,038 --> 00:11:19,067
Jim?

170
00:11:19,068 --> 00:11:22,880
My full name. Come on! Who am I?!

171
00:11:22,881 --> 00:11:24,021
I don't know.

172
00:11:24,022 --> 00:11:25,412
He's  the guy from the time capsule.

173
00:11:25,413 --> 00:11:26,914
Jimmy Edwards.

174
00:11:27,690 --> 00:11:29,419
You're Jimmy Edwards,

175
00:11:29,576 --> 00:11:32,897
and you're a good guy, and you are better than this.

176
00:11:32,898 --> 00:11:36,293
Just shut up! All of you, just shut up and sit down!

177
00:11:36,294 --> 00:11:40,002
Jimmy, seven hostages in the tutor center? That's not you.

178
00:11:40,003 --> 00:11:41,195
What are you doing? What's in your pocket?

179
00:11:41,196 --> 00:11:42,310
- Nothing.
- What's in your pocket?

180
00:11:42,311 --> 00:11:43,633
Stop pointing the gun at her, all right?

181
00:11:43,634 --> 00:11:44,589
It's just my phone, okay?

182
00:11:44,590 --> 00:11:46,280
Give it to me! Throw it here.

183
00:11:49,566 --> 00:11:54,558
Oh, Haley, I used to like you.

184
00:11:55,035 --> 00:11:58,348
Hi, 911? Here's the thing.

185
00:11:58,349 --> 00:12:01,650
If anyone comes even remotely close to this school,

186
00:12:01,651 --> 00:12:03,651
we start shooting students.

187
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:05,141
You hear me?

188
00:12:05,143 --> 00:12:08,515
You come in here, your kids die.

189
00:12:10,180 --> 00:12:12,775
All right, I want everyone's cellphones! Let's go!

190
00:12:13,156 --> 00:12:16,056
And you, missy pepper spray, roll it over here.

191
00:12:16,059 --> 00:12:18,334
The baseball bat, too. Come on!

192
00:12:20,995 --> 00:12:22,213
Where's your phone, Scott?

193
00:12:22,214 --> 00:12:24,093
I don't have it with me.

194
00:12:25,015 --> 00:12:27,285
You can check me if you want.

195
00:12:27,647 --> 00:12:29,426
Just tape the line.

196
00:12:36,767 --> 00:12:38,119
You're kidding me, right?

197
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:41,052
How the hell can a kid just waltz into a high school with a handgun?

198
00:12:41,053 --> 00:12:43,343
Where the hell is the security, the metal detectors?

199
00:12:43,344 --> 00:12:47,174
Security guards carry nightsticks, Dan. Handguns scare people.

200
00:12:47,175 --> 00:12:49,186
They need probable cause to shake a kid down

201
00:12:49,187 --> 00:12:51,445
because god forbid we violate their rights.

202
00:12:51,446 --> 00:12:53,642
And as far as metal detectors go, the school board --

203
00:12:53,643 --> 00:12:54,925
which I believe you're on --

204
00:12:54,926 --> 00:12:55,941
voted against them.

205
00:12:55,942 --> 00:12:57,528
Voted against them? Why?

206
00:12:57,529 --> 00:12:59,590
Because they make the school look unsafe.

207
00:12:59,591 --> 00:13:03,244
911's got a possible identification on one of the shooters.

208
00:13:03,436 --> 00:13:04,967
Jimmy Edwards?

209
00:13:08,385 --> 00:13:10,242
Look, I just want to go home, okay?

210
00:13:10,243 --> 00:13:11,736
Not without a parent.

211
00:13:11,737 --> 00:13:14,145
But my parents don't live here.

212
00:13:14,146 --> 00:13:16,570
Then I guess you'll be here for a while.

213
00:13:19,093 --> 00:13:20,594
Come on, Lucas.

214
00:13:20,694 --> 00:13:21,677
Jimmy Edwards ?

215
00:13:21,678 --> 00:13:22,936
Mary Edwards?

216
00:13:23,168 --> 00:13:24,152
Yes.

217
00:13:24,153 --> 00:13:25,496
Would you come with me, please?

218
00:13:25,497 --> 00:13:27,031
Is my son okay?

219
00:13:27,415 --> 00:13:29,915
Please just come with me, ma'am.

220
00:13:36,805 --> 00:13:38,256
God!

221
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:44,211
You're bleeding pretty good. We're gonna have to put some pressure on it.

222
00:13:45,301 --> 00:13:48,566
Luke, it was your friend,

223
00:13:49,068 --> 00:13:51,628
the one from the time capsule.

224
00:13:52,509 --> 00:13:54,712
He had the gun.

225
00:13:55,870 --> 00:13:58,987
But he didn't look evil or angry.

226
00:13:59,774 --> 00:14:01,914
He just looked scared.

227
00:14:09,522 --> 00:14:11,969
All right, nobody crosses that line.

228
00:14:11,970 --> 00:14:13,753
If  anybody does...

229
00:14:14,218 --> 00:14:15,442
just don't.

230
00:14:15,443 --> 00:14:18,371
Or what, Jim? Would you really do that?

231
00:14:18,372 --> 00:14:19,644
Would you shoot us?

232
00:14:19,645 --> 00:14:21,240
Don't talk to me, Haley.

233
00:14:21,241 --> 00:14:22,911
'Cause I don't think that you would.

234
00:14:22,912 --> 00:14:25,438
Right. When's the last time we hung out?

235
00:14:25,862 --> 00:14:29,794
You're as bad as my best friend Mouth, who totally blew me off!

236
00:14:29,795 --> 00:14:31,546
You didn't want to do anything.

237
00:14:31,547 --> 00:14:34,863
Tell yourself that, but you changed and you know it.

238
00:14:34,864 --> 00:14:37,196
You became just like the rest of them.

239
00:14:37,197 --> 00:14:38,764
Don't do that.

240
00:14:38,939 --> 00:14:41,707
Don't make him feel guilty for living his life.

241
00:14:41,708 --> 00:14:43,488
This is not his fault.

242
00:14:43,587 --> 00:14:44,804
This is your fault.

243
00:14:44,805 --> 00:14:46,648
No, it's your fault.

244
00:14:46,787 --> 00:14:49,192
You think this is what I wanted?

245
00:14:49,642 --> 00:14:53,406
You think I got up today and wanted this?

246
00:14:53,517 --> 00:14:55,635
I just wanted it to stop.

247
00:14:57,690 --> 00:15:00,156
This is kind of screwed up, huh, Skills?

248
00:15:00,157 --> 00:15:02,160
It's more than "kind of," dog.

249
00:15:02,161 --> 00:15:03,194
For real.

250
00:15:03,195 --> 00:15:05,744
We could charge you, you know?

251
00:15:06,013 --> 00:15:09,711
If we all charged you at once, no way you shoot us all.

252
00:15:09,712 --> 00:15:11,982
Yeah, you're probably right, but...

253
00:15:13,038 --> 00:15:15,087
who's gonna be first?

254
00:15:15,273 --> 00:15:20,135
Besides, even if you get past me, the others will get you.

255
00:15:20,350 --> 00:15:21,701
Are there others, Jim?

256
00:15:21,702 --> 00:15:23,072
No, no, no.

257
00:15:23,073 --> 00:15:24,605
I was out there.

258
00:15:24,606 --> 00:15:25,747
It's just you.

259
00:15:25,748 --> 00:15:27,411
You  think so?

260
00:15:27,540 --> 00:15:30,496
Do you really think I'm the only one?

261
00:15:32,162 --> 00:15:34,206
Then ask yourself this --

262
00:15:35,254 --> 00:15:39,318
you ever treat someone like crap in this school or left anyone out?

263
00:15:39,487 --> 00:15:43,962
You ever broken up with someone in the time it takes to pass a note and disappear?

264
00:15:43,963 --> 00:15:46,327
Or talk trash behind their back?

265
