00:15:48,603 --> 00:15:52,641
you know, while you worry about the big game or the prom or

267
00:15:53,033 --> 00:15:55,827
or the bake sale for the pep club.

268
00:15:55,828 --> 00:16:00,656
You ask yourselves that, and then you tell me, is anyone else out there.

269
00:16:02,863 --> 00:16:05,074
Whose phone is that?

270
00:16:05,075 --> 00:16:06,314
It's mine.

271
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:08,282
It's the ringtone for my mom.

272
00:16:08,283 --> 00:16:10,429
God, I hate that song.

273
00:16:11,448 --> 00:16:13,866
Yeah, open your eyes. Your son's a dick!

274
00:16:15,223 --> 00:16:16,575
Open your eyes!

275
00:16:17,942 --> 00:16:19,447
Open your eyes!

276
00:16:20,339 --> 00:16:21,768
Open your eyes!

277
00:16:23,305 --> 00:16:24,994
Do you think I'm playing around?

278
00:16:24,995 --> 00:16:26,953
Whoa, whoa, just chill out.

279
00:16:26,954 --> 00:16:28,171
Jimmy, please.

280
00:16:28,172 --> 00:16:28,999
You're not gonna do it.

281
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,819
Shut up. Don't push me.

282
00:16:30,820 --> 00:16:32,204
Skills, help me out here.

283
00:16:32,205 --> 00:16:33,267
Yo, Marcus, man.

284
00:16:33,268 --> 00:16:34,425
Better back him up!

285
00:16:34,426 --> 00:16:35,804
- Listen to him!
- He's not gonna do it!

286
00:16:35,805 --> 00:16:37,037
- Marcus!
- What?!

287
00:16:39,504 --> 00:16:40,847
That help you out?

288
00:16:41,751 --> 00:16:43,430
Behind the line!

289
00:16:43,665 --> 00:16:45,398
Move, Skills!

290
00:16:45,749 --> 00:16:47,681
Get behind the line!

291
00:16:52,794 --> 00:16:55,403
Look, Reeves, with all due respect,

292
00:16:55,404 --> 00:16:56,623
you know where this Edwards kid is at.

293
00:16:56,624 --> 00:16:59,520
You need to get control of the situation and get somebody into that school.

294
00:16:59,521 --> 00:17:01,473
We know where one kid's at.

295
00:17:01,474 --> 00:17:03,346
Now, can you guarantee me that's the only kid

296
00:17:03,347 --> 00:17:06,144
who walked into that school with a gun this morning?

297
00:17:06,335 --> 00:17:08,717
Look, mayor, this is a static situation.

298
00:17:08,718 --> 00:17:11,325
If and when it becomes active, we will intervene.

299
00:17:11,326 --> 00:17:14,474
But until then, there's a mandated procedure.

300
00:17:14,475 --> 00:17:17,651
We secure the area, we wait for the crisis negotiator,

301
00:17:17,652 --> 00:17:21,274
and we pray to god that Tree Hill High doesn't become just another catchphrase

302
00:17:21,275 --> 00:17:24,594
that people only whisper about for the rest of time.

303
00:17:27,712 --> 00:17:30,211
Is it true? Is it Jimmy Edwards?

304
00:17:30,212 --> 00:17:31,404
One of them.

305
00:17:32,226 --> 00:17:35,006
I know him. He's not a bad kid.

306
00:17:35,641 --> 00:17:37,011
He is now.

307
00:17:43,731 --> 00:17:44,953
Hey.

308
00:17:45,887 --> 00:17:48,474
I don't even know what Lucas is wearing.

309
00:17:48,853 --> 00:17:53,244
The policeman asked, and I couldn't even tell him what Lucas was wearing.

310
00:17:53,407 --> 00:17:56,639
I didn't even get a chance to say goodbye.

311
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:58,033
You're not gonna have to.

312
00:17:59,159 --> 00:18:00,804
You're not gonna have to.

313
00:18:05,296 --> 00:18:09,864
The truth is, every day I have to come to this school

314
00:18:10,081 --> 00:18:12,771
is one less day I have to come back.

315
00:18:12,772 --> 00:18:15,344
That's excellent. I want to air this with a live feed.

316
00:18:15,345 --> 00:18:18,036
I'll get student reactions, their emotions.

317
00:18:18,037 --> 00:18:19,383
There's gold here.

318
00:18:21,186 --> 00:18:23,667
Little insensitive, don't you think?

319
00:18:23,819 --> 00:18:25,626
And you might be?

320
00:18:25,627 --> 00:18:28,391
Brooke Davis, Student Council President.

321
00:18:33,195 --> 00:18:35,468
I'm here with Student Council President Brooke Davis.

322
00:18:35,469 --> 00:18:40,061
Brooke, can you put into words how you might be feeling about this tragedy?

323
00:18:40,984 --> 00:18:43,555
You should be ashamed of yourself.

324
00:18:50,115 --> 00:18:51,818
Might wanna duck.

325
00:18:52,057 --> 00:18:53,993
No, it's just the reporters.

326
00:18:53,994 --> 00:18:56,010
We're all part of the circus now.

327
00:18:56,011 --> 00:18:57,756
Can I ask you a question?

328
00:18:57,952 --> 00:18:59,708
What do you want to happen?

329
00:19:00,041 --> 00:19:01,892
What do I want to happen?

330
00:19:01,924 --> 00:19:07,145
Uh, yeah, I want to crap a million dollars and a plane ticket to Bolivia.

331
00:19:07,146 --> 00:19:09,055
Maybe you could just give up.

332
00:19:09,056 --> 00:19:12,005
Oh, yeah, that's it. I'll just call a do-over.

333
00:19:12,006 --> 00:19:16,377
Why not? You didn't hurt anybody... did you?

334
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:19,371
Did you shoot anyone, Jimmy?

335
00:19:21,552 --> 00:19:23,022
I don't know.

336
00:19:23,375 --> 00:19:25,419
You don't have a record, Jim.

337
00:19:25,420 --> 00:19:27,739
You're a good student, and you're a minor.

338
00:19:27,740 --> 00:19:31,409
Yeah. Maybe this isn't as bad as you think.

339
00:19:34,208 --> 00:19:35,674
You're kidding, right?

340
00:19:35,675 --> 00:19:37,959
The guy shot up a school.

341
00:19:37,960 --> 00:19:39,102
Would  you shut up, man?

342
00:19:39,103 --> 00:19:40,495
You shut up.

343
00:19:40,824 --> 00:19:42,518
I'm not lying for him.

344
00:19:42,523 --> 00:19:44,764
He pointed a gun at my head and threatened to kill me.

345
00:19:44,765 --> 00:19:46,581
I hope they fry his ass.

346
00:19:46,882 --> 00:19:48,986
What's wrong with you?

347
00:19:49,452 --> 00:19:51,249
He's just a kid.

348
00:19:52,619 --> 00:19:56,266
We're all just kids, and we just have this life.

349
00:19:56,267 --> 00:19:59,199
And the things you say and do, we feel that.

350
00:19:59,792 --> 00:20:03,101
How can you have so much hate in your heart?

351
00:20:03,687 --> 00:20:08,140
How can you act like it doesn't matter? It does matter.

352
00:20:09,274 --> 00:20:11,319
What happened to us, huh?

353
00:20:11,566 --> 00:20:15,496
We're just kids. We can't be like this.

354
00:20:15,497 --> 00:20:17,740
It's not possible.

355
00:20:19,989 --> 00:20:22,197
It's 700 days --

356
00:20:22,919 --> 00:20:24,389
high school --

357
00:20:25,273 --> 00:20:28,127
out of 20,000 or 30,000.

358
00:20:28,128 --> 00:20:30,443
Can't you see past that?

359
00:20:31,324 --> 00:20:33,874
It's only 700 days.

360
00:20:34,314 --> 00:20:38,920
Yeah, and how many of these days do I get back?

361
00:20:40,306 --> 00:20:43,072
Do I get back the days I got spit on?

362
00:20:43,487 --> 00:20:47,340
Or the day I learned to look at the floor when I walked the halls?

363
00:20:47,341 --> 00:20:49,713
Or how about the day my dad came to pick me up

364
00:20:49,714 --> 00:20:52,230
and saw me getting my ass kicked on the quad

365
00:20:52,231 --> 00:20:54,766
and realized his son was a loser?

366
00:20:56,940 --> 00:21:00,839
You ever see the look in your father's eyes when he realizes that?

367
00:21:02,026 --> 00:21:04,117
Do I get that day back?

368
00:21:04,675 --> 00:21:08,389
'Cause I saw that same look the day he left me and my mom.

369
00:21:11,772 --> 00:21:13,425
That sucks, man.

370
00:21:14,503 --> 00:21:15,631
I'm sorry.

371
00:21:16,027 --> 00:21:18,132
That's great. You're sorry.

372
00:21:18,834 --> 00:21:20,690
You can forget it!

373
00:21:21,767 --> 00:21:23,911
This ain't "breakfast club."

374
00:21:23,912 --> 00:21:28,128
We're not all gonna fire up a joint and be pals. I mean, let's face it.

375
00:21:28,129 --> 00:21:31,893
This is the most any of us have talked in four years.

376
00:21:31,894 --> 00:21:36,097
And we all know if I don't have this gun, it never happens!

377
00:21:36,619 --> 00:21:38,309
People suck, okay?

378
00:21:39,867 --> 00:21:41,616
It's just high school, man.

379
00:21:43,107 --> 00:21:45,797
Yeah, there's always college, right?

380
00:21:46,964 --> 00:21:48,677
M.I.T.

381
00:21:48,951 --> 00:21:50,431
Remember, Jim?

382
00:21:51,540 --> 00:21:53,464
They rejected me.

383
00:21:53,740 --> 00:21:55,344
And you know why?

384
00:21:55,771 --> 00:21:57,885
Not enough activities.

385
00:21:59,598 --> 00:22:02,946
I guess Tree Hill Fight Club doesn't count.

386
00:22:03,126 --> 00:22:05,838
One school is not the end of the world.

387
00:22:06,017 --> 00:22:07,865
It is for me.

388
00:22:07,866 --> 00:22:09,822
It's the end of my world.

389
00:22:09,991 --> 00:22:11,492
So what?

390
00:22:11,615 --> 00:22:14,790
All this because you didn't into college?

391
00:22:15,203 --> 00:22:16,885
All this because you're not popular?

392
00:22:16,886 --> 00:22:18,203
No.

393
00:22:20,404 --> 00:22:23,229
All this because I'm tired of it.

394
00:22:34,652 --> 00:22:36,852
I'm tired, Luke.

395
00:22:36,938 --> 00:22:38,570
Are you tired?

396
00:22:39,290 --> 00:22:42,740
Yeah, but you got to stay awake, all right?

397
00:22:42,949 --> 00:22:44,523
Talk to me.

398
00:22:45,418 --> 00:22:47,234
Tell me about a good day.

399
00:22:50,461 --> 00:22:55,510
We had a snow day -- sixth grade. Do you remember?

400
00:22:57,018 --> 00:23:04,307
It was like this whole other world just came in overnight and took ours away.

401
00:23:05,545 --> 00:23:09,221
And Brooke -- she came over.

402
00:23:09,454 --> 00:23:13,749
We made a snow fort with a tunnel.

403
00:23:15,980 --> 00:23:19,361
And we stayed inside there all day.

404
00:23:20,887 --> 00:23:27,023
And it seemed so safe, like everything was okay.

405
00:23:27,815 --> 00:23:31,801
Like everything our world was about to become,

406
00:23:32,245 --> 00:23:35,271
maybe we could just stop it

407
00:23:36,386 --> 00:23:40,006
and stay little kids for one more day.

408
00:23:42,450 --> 00:23:45,099
But then it got cold...

409
00:23:46,686 --> 00:23:48,826
kind of like now.

410
00:23:51,175 --> 00:23:53,377
They're gonna come now.

411
00:23:54,443 --> 00:23:55,607
Who?

412
00:23:55,608 --> 00:23:57,202
All of them.

413
00:23:58,443 --> 00:24:00,456
The reporters

414
00:24:01,171 --> 00:24:05,181
and the psychologists and the analysts

415
00:24:05,182 --> 00:24:08,661
and the so-called experts.

416
00:24:09,080 --> 00:24:12,448
They're gonna try to make sense of this,

417
00:24:12,763 --> 00:24:15,960
but they're not gonna be able to.

418
00:24:17,158 --> 00:24:20,268
And even if we do make it out of here,

419
00:24:20,427 --> 00:24:23,723
we're always gonna carry it with us.

420
00:24:24,658 --> 00:24:27,347
It's never gonna be the same.

421
00:24:33,799 --> 00:24:36,223
It's not glass, is it?

422
00:24:36,856 --> 00:24:38,510
In my leg?

423
00:24:40,895 --> 00:24:42,279
No.

424
00:24:43,601 --> 00:24:45,345
It's a bullet.

425
00:24:46,893 --> 00:24:50,072
Now, I may have to get you out of here, okay?

426
00:24:51,379 --> 00:24:53,893
But nothing will happen to you.

427
00:24:54,191 --> 00:24:55,809
I promise.

428
00:24:57,236 --> 00:25:00,073
You're always saving me.

429
00:25:01,136 --> 00:25:03,334
Somebody's got to.

430
00:25:06,969 --> 00:25:14,842
If I say I love you right now, will you hold it against me?

431
00:25:14,843 --> 00:25:17,627
'Cause I've lost a lot of blood.

432
00:25:20,621 --> 00:25:22,099
Come here.

433
00:25:32,694 --> 00:25:36,040
Just in case you can't keep your promise.

434
00:25:47,423 --> 00:25:49,089
That warm your heart?

435
00:25:51,421 --> 00:25:54,037
Do you think America would tune in for that every night?

436
00:25:54,038 --> 00:25:56,533
Have you seen the ratings for "7th Heaven"?

437
00:25:57,759 --> 00:26:01,119
We're a country obsessed with tragedy, Brooke.

438
00:26:01,708 --> 00:26:06,452
So if examining tragedy makes me part of the problem, then so be it.

439
00:26:06,764 --> 00:26:08,629
But let me ask you something.

440
00:26:08,926 --> 00:26:13,034
How much time have you spent with Jimmy Edwards over the last four years?

441
00:26:16,224 --> 00:26:19,380
So maybe I'm not the only one who should be ashamed.

442
00:26:29,138 --> 00:26:30,454
Brooke?

443
00:26:30,778 --> 00:26:32,651
Hi, I'm Glenda's mom.

444
00:26:32,652 --> 00:26:34,614
I was wondering if you had seen her.

445
00:26:34,615 --> 00:26:38,163
Um... I'm sorry. I don't know anyone n--

446
00:26:38,164 --> 00:26:42,494
Glenda Farrell. She's in your class. She said you were friends.

447
00:26:44,730 --> 00:26:48,770
Glenda. I thought you said Brenda. I'm sorry.

448
00:26:48,771 --> 00:26:51,957
Sure, I'll find her.

449
00:27:21,309 --> 00:27:23,470
I need to get out of here.

450
00:27:23,918 --> 00:27:26,618
Yeah, me too. Can we get a hall pass?

451
00:27:26,882 --> 00:27:30,719
Has it only been an hour? It seems like it's been longer than that.

452
00:27:30,720 --> 00:27:32,972
I have current events this period.

453
00:27:32,973 --> 00:27:34,792
I think this counts.

454
00:27:36,155 --> 00:27:39,815
Edwards, where are you supposed to be right now?

455
00:27:40,452 --> 00:27:43,702
I'm supposed to be in A.P. english, but I stopped going.

456
00:27:43,703 --> 00:27:44,938
Why?

457
00:27:44,944 --> 00:27:48,144
Well, because I missed a couple weeks about three months ago,

458
00:27:48,145 --> 00:27:50,041
and I couldn't catch up.

459
00:27:52,075 --> 00:27:54,183
See, one day I spent a whole day in this school

460
00:27:54,184 --> 00:27:58,442
without a single person looking at me or talking to me,

461
00:27:58,443 --> 00:28:03,341
and I realized that was the best day I'd had in a long time --

462
00:28:03,496 --> 00:28:06,374
the day that nobody noticed me at all.

463
00:28:06,836 --> 00:28:09,299
The day I stopped being there --

464
00:28:09,793 --> 00:28:12,078
that was the best day.

465
00:28:13,632 --> 00:28:19,601
Well, that was kind of depressing, so I went home and took an antidepressant.

466
00:28:19,721 --> 00:28:22,010
And then I took another one,

467
00:28:22,652 --> 00:28:25,381
and then for fun I took 12 more.

468
00:28:27,602 --> 00:28:30,829
My mom and the doctors called it an accident.

469
00:28:31,184 --> 00:28:34,750
And then two weeks later when I got back to school...

470
00:28:36,177 --> 00:28:37,745
nobody noticed.

471
00:28:38,714 --> 00:28:41,722
It was like I never left.

472
00:28:44,422 --> 00:28:48,493
I guess that's the upside of not being there in the first place, right?

473
00:28:48,772 --> 00:28:51,577
Nobody misses you when you're gone.

474
00:28:53,841 --> 00:28:56,356
It's not supposed to be this way.

475
00:28:58,932 --> 00:29:01,586
The artists and the scientists and the poets --

476
00:29:01,587 --> 00:29:03,961
none of them fit in at 17.

477
00:29:06,122 --> 00:29:08,541
You're supposed to get past it.

478
00:29:09,403 --> 00:29:13,973
Adults, they see kids killing kids, and

479
00:29:13,974 --> 00:29:17,568
they know it's a tragedy because they used to be those kids --

480
00:29:17,643 --> 00:29:21,098
the bullies and the beaten and the loners.

481
00:29:25,072 --> 00:29:27,628
You're supposed to get past it.

482
00:29:28,203 --> 00:29:31,611
You're supposed to live long enough to take it back.

483
00:29:33,893 --> 00:29:36,096
Just take it all back.

484
00:29:41,940 --> 00:29:43,368
Excuse me.

485
00:29:45,139 --> 00:29:46,706
Are you Glenda?

486
00:29:47,586 --> 00:29:48,632
Yeah.

487
00:29:49,209 --> 00:29:50,422
Okay.

488
00:29:50,540 --> 00:29:52,134
Your mom is here.

489
00:29:52,687 --> 00:29:55,627
Oh, I know. I just --

490
00:29:56,209 --> 00:29:58,829
I thought I'd sit here a little while longer.

491
00:30:01,778 --> 00:30:03,140
Why?

492
00:30:04,363 --> 00:30:07,195
Sometimes I think she takes me for granted...

493
00:30:08,917 --> 00:30:11,384
like it wouldn't matter if I wasn't here.

494
00:30:13,001 --> 00:30:15,874
I guess I just wanted her to be afraid of losing me,

495
00:30:15,875 --> 00:30:19,758
you know, feel it a little.

496
00:30:21,787 --> 00:30:24,492
I don't know. That's pretty horrible, isn't it?

497
00:30:26,001 --> 00:30:27,520
Not really.

498
00:30:31,367 --> 00:30:33,537
Well, I guess I better go.

499
00:30:36,281 --> 00:30:37,782
Hey, Glenda?

500
00:30:40,949 --> 00:30:43,325
I'm really sorry I don't know you.

501
00:30:44,291 --> 00:30:45,585
That's okay.

502
00:30:46,424 --> 00:30:47,785
I know you.

503
00:31:00,675 --> 00:31:03,436
Hey, I'm really sorry to call.

504
00:31:07,296 --> 00:31:10,137
That was Brooke. They won't release her without an adult, but I --

505
00:31:10,138 --> 00:31:12,571
It's okay. I'll wait here.

506
00:31:13,597 --> 00:31:17,126
Hey, it's gonna be okay.

507
00:31:17,450 --> 00:31:20,232
I'm not gonna let anything happen to our boy.

508
00:31:22,060 --> 00:31:23,151
Come here.

509
00:31:39,053 --> 00:31:41,224
You shouldn't have come back for me.

510
00:31:41,225 --> 00:31:44,632
I love you for doing it, but I wish you were safe.

511
00:31:44,904 --> 00:31:47,448
I don't want to be safe without you.

512
00:31:47,836 --> 00:31:53,011
I heard what you said, Scott, in the time capsule about Haley.

513
00:31:53,973 --> 00:31:57,044
Guys like you can get away with it.

514
00:31:57,402 --> 00:31:59,409
Guys like me, huh?

515
00:31:59,857 --> 00:32:02,414
You can pass judgment about guys like me all you want,

516
00:32:02,415 --> 00:32:05,025
but somebody stereotypes you, and there's gunplay?

517
00:32:05,026 --> 00:32:06,485
Whatever.

518
00:32:06,549 --> 00:32:09,730
Your worst day in this place would be my best day.

519
00:32:09,731 --> 00:32:13,451
Okay, okay, maybe so, all right? Maybe it is easier for me and my friends.

520
00:32:13,452 --> 00:32:16,302
That doesn't make what you're doing right, does it?

521
00:32:16,303 --> 00:32:18,775
This is wrong, man, all of this.

522
00:32:18,776 --> 00:32:20,534
I think you know that.

523
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:24,294
Abby, are you okay?

524
00:32:24,295 --> 00:32:25,963
I'm fine.

525
00:32:32,331 --> 00:32:34,065
No, you're not.

526
00:32:37,770 --> 00:32:40,164
You're diabetic? Where's you insulin?

527
00:32:40,165 --> 00:32:41,700
- What's wrong with her?
- She's diabetic.

528
00:32:41,701 --> 00:32:42,937
Where is it?

