00:32:42,938 --> 00:32:45,972
In my locker across the quad. I'm sorry.

530
00:32:45,973 --> 00:32:49,093
No, forget it. It's impossible.

531
00:32:49,094 --> 00:32:50,707
You could let her go.

532
00:32:50,708 --> 00:32:52,427
Yeah, you got us, dog.

533
00:32:52,428 --> 00:32:54,291
Jimmy, she's really sick.

534
00:32:54,292 --> 00:32:55,435
Let her go, Jim.

535
00:32:55,436 --> 00:32:57,085
Yeah, let her go.

536
00:32:57,324 --> 00:32:59,368
Unbelievable!

537
00:33:00,929 --> 00:33:03,433
All right, just you. Come on.

538
00:33:03,434 --> 00:33:04,431
Come on, Abby.

539
00:33:06,660 --> 00:33:08,198
Hey, I'm sick, too.

540
00:33:08,199 --> 00:33:09,882
Seriously. I feel terrible.

541
00:33:09,896 --> 00:33:11,556
Stay behind the line!

542
00:33:11,557 --> 00:33:12,769
Come on.

543
00:33:21,564 --> 00:33:24,267
Go on before I change my mind!

544
00:33:24,898 --> 00:33:26,691
I'm scared.

545
00:33:26,729 --> 00:33:28,162
Of what?

546
00:33:28,692 --> 00:33:30,333
The others.

547
00:33:31,204 --> 00:33:33,276
Are there others, Jim?

548
00:33:35,001 --> 00:33:37,825
Does this feel well-planned to you?

549
00:33:42,525 --> 00:33:44,107
Go.

550
00:34:33,132 --> 00:34:36,151
Hey, what are you doing?! You said you didn't have a phone!

551
00:34:36,152 --> 00:34:37,685
Who'd you call?!

552
00:34:38,417 --> 00:34:40,611
They better not come in here!

553
00:34:41,871 --> 00:34:43,606
I just got a text message from Nathan.

554
00:34:43,607 --> 00:34:45,539
Is he in there? Is Lucas with him?

555
00:34:46,261 --> 00:34:49,557
He says this kid is the only one. They're in the tutor center.

556
00:34:49,902 --> 00:34:51,634
Just Jimmy Edwards, huh?

557
00:34:52,349 --> 00:34:55,279
Look, Danny, I know we've had our difference lately,

558
00:34:55,280 --> 00:34:57,982
but you got to let me try to talk to him.

559
00:34:58,006 --> 00:35:00,506
I know this kid. If they go in there,

560
00:35:00,560 --> 00:35:03,613
he's gonna get spooked, and this thing is gonna turn out bad.

561
00:35:03,949 --> 00:35:05,249
Please. Just let me try.

562
00:35:05,250 --> 00:35:06,745
No way. It's too dangerous.

563
00:35:06,746 --> 00:35:07,771
Dan?

564
00:35:08,845 --> 00:35:10,048
Please?

565
00:35:10,575 --> 00:35:12,326
You can get me in there.

566
00:35:12,722 --> 00:35:14,443
Nobody has to know.

567
00:35:17,292 --> 00:35:19,496
I should've known it was all about the gun.

568
00:35:19,497 --> 00:35:21,956
So, what -- do I have to pull the trigger again for you to take me seriously?

569
00:35:21,957 --> 00:35:22,832
No!

570
00:35:22,833 --> 00:35:24,097
Edwards, come on, man.

571
00:35:24,098 --> 00:35:28,704
I promise you, whoever steps into that hallway is gonna die.

572
00:35:30,639 --> 00:35:31,902
I got you.

573
00:35:41,292 --> 00:35:43,843
I guess that's my cue.

574
00:35:45,667 --> 00:35:46,966
Don't!

575
00:35:48,177 --> 00:35:49,778
Just stop.

576
00:35:49,805 --> 00:35:51,221
Change it.

577
00:35:52,861 --> 00:35:54,112
Don't do this.

578
00:35:54,113 --> 00:35:58,284
Please, Jim. Just turn yourself in. I can go with you.

579
00:35:58,490 --> 00:36:00,516
This can't be happening.

580
00:36:00,517 --> 00:36:03,880
Yo, Edwards, man, it don't have to be like this, dog.

581
00:36:04,457 --> 00:36:07,173
Yeah, I think it does.

582
00:36:12,069 --> 00:36:13,296
Jimmy.

583
00:36:15,759 --> 00:36:18,783
You know, they're gonna remember me as a monster.

584
00:36:20,807 --> 00:36:23,610
I wonder how they'll remember all of you.

585
00:36:55,828 --> 00:36:57,616
Where do you think you're going?!

586
00:37:00,440 --> 00:37:01,375
She's bleeding.

587
00:37:01,376 --> 00:37:04,258
The school's on lockdown!

588
00:37:04,541 --> 00:37:06,142
I know, Jim.

589
00:37:06,825 --> 00:37:09,977
But if I don't get her out of here, she's gonna die.

590
00:37:10,912 --> 00:37:13,167
I didn't mean to hurt her.

591
00:37:14,641 --> 00:37:15,970
We know that, Jimmy.

592
00:37:15,971 --> 00:37:17,977
What the hell is this?!

593
00:37:17,978 --> 00:37:21,106
The school's on lockdown!

594
00:37:21,107 --> 00:37:23,018
Please, Jimmy, just --

595
00:37:23,216 --> 00:37:27,827
please just let them go, and you and I can talk about this.

596
00:37:28,465 --> 00:37:30,492
She's hurt, Jimmy.

597
00:37:30,616 --> 00:37:32,687
I didn't mean it.

598
00:37:34,993 --> 00:37:36,219
I know.

599
00:37:41,987 --> 00:37:43,594
Go on, Luke.

600
00:37:51,038 --> 00:37:52,835
- Keith --
- Luke...

601
00:37:54,361 --> 00:37:56,464
I love you. Now go.

602
00:38:07,154 --> 00:38:09,782
Why don't you just hand me that gun, Jimmy,

603
00:38:09,783 --> 00:38:11,629
and we can just follow them out of here?

604
00:38:11,630 --> 00:38:13,141
I can't.

605
00:38:14,044 --> 00:38:16,742
Well, I'm not gonna leave you here, son.

606
00:38:18,445 --> 00:38:21,142
I'm not gonna do that, and I'll tell you why.

607
00:38:22,164 --> 00:38:24,069
Because I've been there.

608
00:38:24,481 --> 00:38:28,174
I've bought the gun, and I planned on using it, okay?

609
00:38:28,175 --> 00:38:29,941
I've been there,

610
00:38:29,953 --> 00:38:31,944
and I want to tell you something.

611
00:38:33,640 --> 00:38:35,194
It gets better.

612
00:38:35,195 --> 00:38:37,839
Not this. It can't.

613
00:38:37,840 --> 00:38:39,377
It does, Jimmy.

614
00:38:39,378 --> 00:38:43,467
That pain in your stomach, that pain in your heart, it goes away.

615
00:38:43,468 --> 00:38:48,214
That voice in your head that's saying there's no way out, it's wrong, Jimmy.

616
00:38:48,688 --> 00:38:52,817
Would you please -- please just believe me. It gets better.

617
00:38:52,818 --> 00:38:55,868
It won't! Not after this!

618
00:38:55,869 --> 00:39:00,025
I can't take this back! I can't erase this!

619
00:39:02,170 --> 00:39:03,811
She's gonna die.

620
00:39:04,937 --> 00:39:06,861
You don't know that.

621
00:39:12,624 --> 00:39:14,120
I just --

622
00:39:14,387 --> 00:39:15,822
I wanted --

623
00:39:16,313 --> 00:39:19,065
I wanted them to leave me alone.

624
00:39:19,533 --> 00:39:24,086
I just -- I wanted them to like me.

625
00:39:25,245 --> 00:39:28,488
I understand, son. It's what we all want.

626
00:39:28,808 --> 00:39:30,903
It's all any of us wants.

627
00:39:33,520 --> 00:39:35,553
I'm not here.

628
00:39:37,750 --> 00:39:40,578
- I'm not here.
- Jimmy, please.

629
00:39:43,601 --> 00:39:47,396
It's gonna be okay, son. It's gonna be okay.

630
00:39:47,397 --> 00:39:49,342
But it hurts!

631
00:39:49,351 --> 00:39:52,735
It hurts. It always hurts!

632
00:39:52,736 --> 00:39:54,112
I know.

633
00:39:57,401 --> 00:39:58,942
Please.

634
00:40:00,365 --> 00:40:01,839
Please.

635
00:40:03,773 --> 00:40:05,946
I'm sorry.

636
00:40:06,028 --> 00:40:07,278
No!

637
00:40:12,129 --> 00:40:14,660
Does this darkness have a name?

638
00:40:16,954 --> 00:40:19,751
This cruelty, this hatred, 

639
00:40:21,488 --> 00:40:23,759
how did it find us?

640
00:40:24,785 --> 00:40:29,469
Did it steal into our lives, or did we seek it out and embrace it?

641
00:40:35,958 --> 00:40:38,027
What happened to us?

642
00:40:39,263 --> 00:40:44,738
That we now send our children into the world like we send young men to war... 

643
00:40:46,914 --> 00:40:49,557
Hoping for their safe return... 

644
00:40:50,306 --> 00:40:53,838
But knowing that some will be lost along the way.

645
00:41:04,670 --> 00:41:06,846
When did we lose our way?

646
00:41:08,678 --> 00:41:13,150
Consumed by the shadows, swallowed whole by the darkness.

647
00:41:14,840 --> 00:41:16,819
He's gone, Danny.

648
00:41:17,943 --> 00:41:20,011
He's gone.

649
00:41:32,051 --> 00:41:34,592
Does this darkness have a name?

650
00:41:43,256 --> 00:41:45,325
Is it your name?

